# KMS: System Overview

The Zama KMS is a distributed threshold cryptography service for TFHE keys. No single party ever holds the complete secret key — DKG, public decryption, user decryption, and CRS generation all run as MPC protocols.

## Deployment modes

| Mode | When |
|------|------|
| Centralized | Single node, plaintext (or HSM/Nitro Enclave) keys. Dev, testing, or sealed-enclave deployments. |
| Threshold | `n ≥ 3t + 1` nodes. Malicious-majority safe — up to `t` actively Byzantine nodes tolerated. |

Both modes expose the same gRPC interface, so the engine choice is transparent to the connector.

## Topology

```text
Gateway (KMSGeneration, Decryption)
    │ events
KMS Connector  ── one per KMS node ──  (only component with both gateway RPC and KMS gRPC)
    │ gRPC, localhost only
KMS Core
    ├─ gRPC service (CoreServiceEndpoint)
    ├─ Engine (CentralizedKms | ThresholdKms)
    ├─ Threshold networking (inter-node mTLS)
    └─ Storage
        ├─ Private vault (encrypted key shares, file or S3)
        ├─ Public keychain (public/server/compression keys, CRS — unencrypted)
        └─ Backup vault (custodian-encrypted)
```

KMS Core is reachable only from its co-located connector — never publicly.

## Components

| Module | Role |
|--------|------|
| `core/service` | gRPC service, two engines (centralized, threshold) |
| `core/threshold-execution` | MPC protocols: DKG, public/user decryption, resharing, CRS |
| `core/threshold-networking` | mTLS-authenticated P2P, session routing, peer discovery via `MpcContext` |
| `core/service/src/vault` | Three storage layers (private, public, backup) |
| `fhevm/kms-connector` | `gw-listener` → PostgreSQL → `kms-worker` (gRPC to Core) → `tx-sender` (back to gateway) |

## Key material

| Material | Holder | Location |
|----------|--------|----------|
| Secret key share | Node-local | Private vault (encrypted) |
| FHE public key | Public | Public keychain |
| Server (bootstrapping) key | Public | Public keychain |
| Compression keys | Public | Public keychain |
| CRS | Public | Public keychain |

## gRPC surface

`CoreServiceEndpoint` covers key generation and preprocessing, public and user decryption, CRS generation, context/epoch management, backup/recovery, and health. See the kms-core gRPC API (not bundled in this skill).

